.TH "Element.cut_event" "JS" "December 19, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Element.cut_event \- Element: cut event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]cut\f[B]\f[R] event of the Clipboard API is fired when
the user has initiated a \[lq]cut\[rq] action through the browser\[cq]s
user interface.
.PP
If the user attempts a cut action on uneditable content, the
\f[CR]cut\f[R] event still fires but the event object contains no data.
.PP
The event\[cq]s default action is to copy the current selection (if any)
to the system clipboard and remove it from the document.
.PP
A handler for this event can \f[I]modify\f[R] the clipboard contents by
calling \f[CR]setData(format, data)\f[R] on the event\[cq]s
\f[CR]ClipboardEvent.clipboardData\f[R] property, and cancelling the
default action using \f[CR]event.preventDefault()\f[R].
.PP
Note though that cancelling the default action will also prevent the
document from being updated.
So an event handler which wants to emulate the default action for
\[lq]cut\[rq] while modifying the clipboard must also manually remove
the selection from the document.
.PP
The handler cannot \f[I]read\f[R] the clipboard data.
.PP
It\[cq]s possible to construct and dispatch a synthetic \f[CR]cut\f[R]
event, but this will not affect the system clipboard or the
document\[cq]s contents.
.PP
This event bubbles, is cancelable and is composed.
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\[dq]cut\[dq], (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {});

oncut = (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {};
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A \f[CR]ClipboardEvent\f[R].
Inherits from \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Live example
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]div\f[R] class=\[dq]source\[dq] contenteditable=\[dq]true\[dq]>Cut text from this box.</\f[B]div\f[R]>
<\f[B]div\f[R] class=\[dq]target\[dq] contenteditable=\[dq]true\[dq]>And paste it into this one.</\f[B]div\f[R]>
.EE
.SS JavaScript
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] source = document.querySelector(\[dq]div.source\[dq]);

source.addEventListener(\[dq]cut\[dq], (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]const\f[R] selection = document.getSelection();
  event.clipboardData.setData(\[dq]text/plain\[dq], selection.toString().toUpperCase());
  selection.deleteFromDocument();
  event.preventDefault();
});
.EE
